      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That sense of emptiness is a profound grief, often called \"existential hollowness,\" where the core self feels lost rather than just buried. It is incredibly painful to feel like a shell, but it is also a sign that your current reality no longer holds the meaning you need. While the pain is real, you have the power to slowly rebuild a life that fits this new, changed version of yourself, even if it feels like starting from scratch.",
      "source": "target",
